{"id": "EUVD-2022-55174", "enisaUuid": "2e4cb3ac-4031-36ea-a47a-533e90e85f2b", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ni2c: designware: use casting of u64 in clock multiplication to avoid overflow\n\nIn functions i2c_dw_scl_lcnt() and i2c_dw_scl_hcnt() may have overflow\nby depending on the values of the given parameters including the ic_clk.\nFor example in our use case where ic_clk is larger than one million,\nmultiplication of ic_clk * 4700 will result in 32 bit overflow.\n\nAdd cast of u64 to the calculation to avoid multiplication overflow, and\nuse the corresponding define for divide.", "datePublished": "2025-03-27T16:42:58", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T17:23:29", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ed173f77fd28a3e4fffc13b3f28687b9eba61157", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2f29d780bd691d20e89e5b35d5e6568607115e94", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9f36aae9e80e79b7a6d62227eaa96935166be9fe", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c8c37bc514514999e62a17e95160ed9ebf75ca8d"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49749"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0d46645b-44d9-316c-9aff-3bc644e230a9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2373f6b9744d5373b886f3ce1a985193cca0a356 <9f36aae9e80e79b7a6d62227eaa96935166be9fe"}, {"id": "1402c3a9-7daf-3a25-93d8-ed2cefe09272", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2373f6b9744d5373b886f3ce1a985193cca0a356 <ed173f77fd28a3e4fffc13b3f28687b9eba61157"}, {"id": "201839ae-54e4-3975-a4e9-72e151d3c021", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.91"}, {"id": "2ad1ed23-a228-31e7-9c0e-f0b315c78ffa", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.9"}, {"id": "30bb7ea8-ccf6-35a2-9e00-c378205ec014", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2373f6b9744d5373b886f3ce1a985193cca0a356 <2f29d780bd691d20e89e5b35d